The paper proposes a new approach for knowledge graph embeddings using hypercomplex representations, specifically quaternion embeddings. This work falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with machine learning techniques for knowledge representation. The use of hypercomplex representations also suggests a focus on geometric and algebraic structures, which aligns with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the use of embeddings for natural language processing tasks, indicating a potential connection to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the proposed approach is evaluated on knowledge graph completion benchmarks, which falls under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
